This is the first exposure to programming & computation class, anything superfluous such as semicolons or the keywords just trips people up and gets in the way of learning.  You have to tell people to ignore all of the extra magic words just to get started, even though they would really like to know what it all means.<p>Look at Java:<p><pre><code>  public class HelloWorld { 
      public static void main(String[] args) {
          System.out.println(&quot;Hello, World&quot;);
      }
  }</code></pre>
C:<p><pre><code>  #import <stdio.h>

  int main() {
    printf(&quot;hello&quot;);
    return 0;
  }
</code></pre>
Python:<p><pre><code>  print &quot;Hello&quot;</code></pre>
